A bank customer has slumped and died after standing in a queue for long hours at a bank in Agbor, Delta State. According to the Tribune on Friday, the yet-to-be-identified man died after waiting for hours to collect his Automated Teller Machine card at the bank in Ika South Local Government Area, Delta State. ALSO READ: Naira drops at official market as demand for FX soars Confirming his death, the state’s Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Bright Edafe, said, “He was not trying to withdraw cash; he came to collect his ATM card.” 